{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"Vsq2MH3oisleK9ceK2iGt","title":"Communication","vault":{"fsPath":"handbook","name":"dendron.handbook"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"handbook.sop.communication","id":"Vsq2MH3oisleK9ceK2iGt","vaultName":"dendron.handbook"},"value":"handbook.people.remote-work","alias":"Hours of Availability","position":{"start":{"line":40,"column":11,"offset":1329},"end":{"line":40,"column":86,"offset":1404},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"handbook.people.remote-work","anchorHeader":"hours-of-availability"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"handbook.sop.communication","id":"Vsq2MH3oisleK9ceK2iGt","vaultName":"dendron.handbook"},"value":"handbook.people.remote-work","alias":"Sync","position":{"start":{"line":41,"column":10,"offset":1414},"end":{"line":41,"column":51,"offset":1455},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"handbook.people.remote-work","anchorHeader":"sync"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"handbook.sop.communication","id":"Vsq2MH3oisleK9ceK2iGt","vaultName":"dendron.handbook"},"value":"handbook.people.remote-work","alias":"Async","position":{"start":{"line":42,"column":11,"offset":1466},"end":{"line":42,"column":54,"offset":1509},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"handbook.people.remote-work","anchorHeader":"async"}},{"from":{"fname":"handbook.people.remote-work","vaultName":"dendron.handbook"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":3,"offset":243},"end":{"line":8,"column":74,"offset":314},"indent":[]},"value":"handbook.sop.communication"}],"anchors":{"summary":{"type":"header","text":"Summary","value":"summary","line":8,"column":0},"best-practice":{"type":"header","text":"Best Practice","value":"best-practice","line":12,"column":0},"in-general":{"type":"header","text":"In General","value":"in-general","line":14,"column":0},"messaging":{"type":"header","text":"Messaging","value":"messaging","line":18,"column":0},"async":{"type":"header","text":"async","value":"async","line":26,"column":0},"priority":{"type":"header","text":"priority","value":"priority","line":29,"column":0},"sync":{"type":"header","text":"sync","value":"sync","line":32,"column":0}},"fname":"handbook.sop.communication","updated":1634606035943,"created":1632795411720,"parent":"842733dd-2e94-4abc-83ca-334fbcf52393","children":[],"data":{},"contentHash":"7a9f0558c52b11253e55c173e64c584b","custom":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"communication\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#communication\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Communication</h1>\n<h2 id=\"summary\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#summary\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Summary</h2>\n<!-- What is this SOP about -->\n<p>How we communicate in an all remote, async first fashion</p>\n<h2 id=\"best-practice\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#best-practice\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Best Practice</h2>\n<h3 id=\"in-general\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#in-general\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>In General</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>If you are sending a message, unless sending during work hours, give people at least <strong>12h</strong> to respond</li>\n<li>If you are receiving a message during the work week, respond within <strong>12h</strong> </li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"messaging\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#messaging\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Messaging</h3>\n<p>We have 3 priorities for messages.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>async</li>\n<li>priority</li>\n<li>sync</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"async\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#async\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>async</h4>\n<p>async messages are not urgent. the recipient has 12h durign work hours to respond. this is the default status of a message unless otherwise marked</p>\n<h4 id=\"priority\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#priority\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>priority</h4>\n<p>priority messages are urgent. the recipient should try to respond within 1h of getting this message during work hours. add <code>#prio</code> after your message to indicate a priority message</p>\n<h4 id=\"sync\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#sync\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>sync</h4>\n<p>sync messages are real time. we almost never use sync messages. add a <code>#sync</code> after your comment to indicate a sync message</p>\n<pre><code>@kevin the latest release needs to be rolled back because of a bug in lookup #sync\n</code></pre>\n<p>Synchronous messages should be reserved for when you need immediate feedback. Some examples of good use cases:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>there's an issue with a feature that is blocking deployment</li>\n<li>there's a critical bug that is actively degrading the Dendron experience</li>\n<li>there's an issue that the current oncall needs to look at during their working hours</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"backlinks\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#backlinks\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Backlinks</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/zBlxjKJ0bFMcLJXhch2U0\">Remote Work</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"27237fd0-4ae1-4e31-9c15-34167fb264d8","title":"Dendron Handbook","vault":{"fsPath":"handbook","name":"dendron.handbook"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[],"anchors":{},"fname":"handbook","updated":1623260668267,